args: Hey, Ria! Lemme just take a quick\nsnap of you, okay? Just this once!
Will these mad protestations never cease?\nI told you, if you seek to wield your\nmagical paintbrush, do so on another.
But I want a pic of YOU, Ria!\nWe're BFFs, and BFFs can never\nhave enough pics together!
I believe such to be a credo\nheld by you alone.
Hey, can I talk to you two for a minute?
There's something I need\nboth of you to see...
Hey, that looks just like Clix!\nWhat's the deal, prince dude?
A child from Rovetelle found it in the\nforest, and the adults were worried\nit might be dangerous.
And so they brought it to you?
Yes. And since it looks just like your\nmagic device, Nadine, I thought you\nmight know something about it.

Oh man, that is wild! I mean, I don't
actually KNOW, but I'm guessing it
came from another world like Clix did.
It doesn't look that dangerous, either...
However, much like your device,\nit may affect the surrounding mana.

On its own, Nadine's device seems
harmless enough. But when placed
in the proximity of a similar device,
I fear the effects could multiply.
If the flow of mana is disturbed overmuch,\nit may even entice the attractions of\nnearby unpleasant entities.
Wait, so having Clix and his brothers\nin the same area might cause FIENDS\nto appear or whatever?!
It is merely a possibility. Though as I\nstated, your device alone should\nmostlike pose no particular issue.
Still, if there's even a possibility\nof something going wrong here,\nwe need to check it out.

Yes, especially if children are involved.
Better to look into the problem and find
your efforts for naught than to ignore it
and rue the day.
Okay, cool! In that case, me and Ria\nwill totally open an investigation.
That would be great. Thank you!
Sweeet! A road trip! Time to hitch up\nour walking pants and get hyyyype!
Oh man, look at the sun comin' through\nthose trees—it's perfect picnic weather!\nLemme just snap a quick pic here...
I pray you have not forgotten our goal.
'Course not! We're out here sniffing around\nto see if any more magical doo-dads have\ncome drifting into our world, yeah?
Still, just because we're investigating\ndoesn't mean we gotta furrow our brows\nand make vinegary looks the whole time.
Then let's make this a FUNvestigation\nby throwing Clix into the mix!
You are free to capture what scenery or\nforest animals you like, but pray do not\ninvolve me with your capering gambols.
Riaaaaa! Girl, why do you hate\nhaving your pic taken so much?
And why are you so desperate to\nsee me captured in your witchery?
Why? Well, I guess I just want to have\nmemories of stuff and whatever.
I told you how me and the fam used to\nmove around all the time, yeah?
I believe you spun a tale to that effect.

Well, since we never stayed in one place
for long, my memory is all kinda...woobly.
Like, I tend to forget about a place the
moment I leave it behind, you know?
I've always hated that, but I never knew\nwhat to DO about it until I found Clix.

Like, when I first started fiddling around
with him, I found a whole bunch of pics
that were already there—I'm guessing
they're from his original owner.
Anyway, they were all pictures of girls\nmy age smiling and having fun and stuff,\nand when I saw 'em, I got MAD jealous.
I wanted something like that, you know?!\nI wanted to have a ton of pictures of me\nand my friends being all BFFs!
...Which is the true reason for your\nfanatical obsession with pictures.
It's not fanatical! I mean, who DOESN'T\nwant to look back on pictures of happy\ntimes or whatever?
Memories fade by their very nature,\nyet that device will keep them as\nfresh as the moment they occurred.
Like I said, it's no good to have your most\nprecious memories fade away. I'd way\nrather have a Clix to keep 'em fresh.
Like, whenever I look at the pictures I\ntook with my mom and dad, it makes\nme SUPER happy!
And now you ken why I do not wish\nto take part in your endeavors.
...Huh? Wait, like, no I DON'T!\nI totally do NOT ken that!
The mana warps anew... Marry, could it\nbe another object drifted into our world?!
Ria? Hey! Get back here, girl! We were\ntotally in the middle of a conversation!
